{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "296625ef",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Getting Started\n",
    "\n",
    "To run this notebook you will first need to download the GW data,\n",
    "\n",
    "`python download_SXSwaveform_data.py`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 56,
   "id": "0bf63705",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import WDM\n",
    "from WDM.code.utils.utils import next_multiple"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d8c512cc",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Here's an example GW waveform. We also compute the frequency of the signal as a function of time."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 57,
   "id": "e5002f6b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "data = np.loadtxt(\"../data/waveform_SXS:BBH:0305_Reh22.txt\")\n",
    "\n",
    "time = data[0]\n",
    "re_strain = data[1]\n",
    "im_strain = data[2]\n",
    "\n",
    "frequency = np.diff(-np.unwrap(np.atan2(im_strain, re_strain)), prepend=0) / np.diff(time, prepend=0) / (2*np.pi)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=2, sharex=True)\n",
    "axes[0].plot(time, re_strain)\n",
    "axes[0].set_xlabel('Time')\n",
    "axes[0].set_ylabel('Strain')\n",
    "axes[0].grid()\n",
    "axes[1].plot(time[100:-200], frequency[100:-200], 'k-')\n",
    "axes[1].set_xlabel('Time')\n",
    "axes[1].set_ylabel('Frequency')\n",
    "axes[1].grid()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 58,
   "id": "8df70f10",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Current length of time series: 7688\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "current_length = len(time)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Current length of time series: {current_length}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "77b7c432",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Let's take a wavelet transform of this using $N_f=512$ frequency slices. \n",
    "The `wdm` object will handle the wavelet transform.\n",
    "We need to pad the signal so that it's length is an even multiple of this number"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 59,
   "id": "e56fca95",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Padded length of time series: 8192\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "dt = np.mean(np.diff(time))\n",
    "\n",
    "Nf = 512\n",
    "\n",
    "N = next_multiple(current_length, 2*Nf)\n",
    "\n",
    "wdm = WDM.code.discrete_wavelet_transform.WDM.WDM_transform(dt=dt, Nf=Nf, N=N, q=8, calc_m0=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "re_strain_padded, mask = wdm.pad_signal(re_strain)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Padded length of time series: {N}\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2894191c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Take the forward discrete wavelet transform (dwt). This transforms from the time domain to the time-frequency domain."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 69,
   "id": "005c19de",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "w = wdm.dwt(re_strain_padded)\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "de137820",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can plot these coefficients in the time-frequency plane. \n",
    "The black line shows the frequency obtained directly from the NR waveform.\n",
    "Note, this doesn't look as beautifully smooth as the oversampled periodograms we are used to looking at, but this is what we want for data analysis."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 62,

   "metadata": {},

   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = wdm.time_frequency_plot(w, part='abs', scale='linear')\n",
    "ax.set_ylim(0,0.1)\n",
    "ax.plot(time[100:-200], frequency[100:-200], color='k', lw=2)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "64e45a88",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Let's take an inverse discrete wavelet transform (idwt). \n",
    "\n",
    "This transforms back into the time domain.\n",
    "We do this to check we can recover the original signal.\n",
    "We will use the mask to get the output back to the original shape."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "9686e999",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Max residual: 0.0010781081917313265\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "re_strain_recovered = wdm.idwt(w)[mask]\n",
    "\n",
    "residuals = re_strain_recovered-re_strain\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Max residual: {np.max(np.abs(residuals))}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "e38b39bb",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots()\n",
    "ax.plot(time, re_strain, label='SXS:BBH:0305')\n",
    "ax.plot(time, re_strain_recovered, label='recovered')\n",
    "ax.plot(time, residuals, 'k:', label='residuals')\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Time (s)')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Strain')\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "ax.grid()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
